Prize scalp: Austria's Dominic Thiem got past an ailing Roger Federer in 1hr 18mins.
Swiss third seed Roger Federer’s Rome Masters bid ended with a 7-6(2), 6-4 third round defeat to Austrian 13th seed Dominic Thiem on Thursday.
Federer admitted on Wednesday he had been surprised to get past second round opponent Alexander Zverev in straight sets.
The 17-time Grand Slam champion only decided to face Thiem at the last minute on Central Court, and the Austrian capitalised to finish off an obviously ailing Federer in 1hr 18mins.
The results: Third round: Men: Dominic Thiem bt Roger Federer 7-6(2), 6-4; Kei Nishikori bt Richard Gasquest 6-1, 6-4; Lucas Pouille bt David Ferrer 6-4, 6-1; Juan Monaco bt Stan Wawrinka 6-7(5), 6-3, 6-4; Rafael Nadal bt Nick Kyrgios 6-7(3), 6-2, 6-4.
Women: Serena Williams bt Christina McHale 7-6(7), 6-1; Svetlana Kuznetsova bt Daria Gavrilova 6-2, 2-6, 6-3; Timea Bacsinszky bt Carla Suarez Navarro 5-7, 7-5, 6-2.